quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,118,"And guided them to the Right Path."
  37,119,"And We left for them (a goodly remembrance) among the later generations."
  37,120,""
  40,61,"Allâh, it is He Who has made the night for you that you may rest therein and the day for you to see. Truly, Allâh is full of Bounty to mankind; yet, most of mankind give no thanks."
  40,62,"That is Allâh, your Lord, the Creator of all things: Lâ ilâha illâ Huwa (none has the right to be worshipped but He). How then are you turning away (from Allâh, by worshipping others instead of Him)?"
  40,63,"Thus were turned away those who used to deny the Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) of Allâh."
  41,40,"Verily, those who turn away from Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc. by attacking, distorting and denying them) are not hidden from Us. Is he who is cast into the Fire better or he who comes secure on the Day of Resurrection? Do what you will. Verily He is All-Seer of what you do (this is a severe threat to the disbelievers{1}).",footnotes:1:[{41:40} See the footnote of {17:97}.]
  41,41,"Verily, those who disbelieved in the Reminder (i.e. the Qur’ân) when it came to them (shall receive the punishment). And verily, it is an honourable well-fortified respected Book (because it is Allâh’s Speech, and He has protected it from corruption. (See V.15:9)"
  41,42,"Falsehood cannot come to it from before it or behind it: (it is) sent down by the All-Wise, Worthy of all praise (Allâh عز وجل)."
  42,25,"And He it is Who accepts repentance from His slaves, and forgives sins, and He knows what you do.{1}",footnotes:1:[{42:25}]
  42,26,"And He answers (the invocation of) those who believe (in the Oneness of Allâh - Islâmic Monotheism) and do righteous good deeds, and gives them increase of His Bounty. And as for the disbelievers, theirs will be a severe torment."
  42,27,"And if Allâh were to enlarge the provision for His slaves, they would surely rebel in the earth, but He sends down by measure as He wills. Verily! He is, in respect of His slaves, the Well-Aware, the All-Seer (of things that benefit them)."
  43,7,"And never came there a Prophet to them but they used to mock at him."
  43,8,"Then We destroyed men stronger (in power) than these - and the example of the ancients has passed away (before them)."
  43,9,"And indeed if you ask them, "